Existing-fact prediction describes the prediction of an object for a subject-relation pair for which the ground truth object already exists in a KB. We will analyse the prediction ability of BERT given existing facts from Wikidata in an automated evaluation, focusing on the recall achieved at 90% precision ({{arxiv_2303_11082_FO0009||FO}}).